claim.claim-text:
4. A method of increasing the strength and endurance of a user with a treadmill, comprising: 
attaching the apparatus of claim 1 to a treadmill, so that the base rests on the ground and is arranged to extend predominantly aft of the user's legs; 
securing the belt about the user's waist; 
securing each collar around the thigh of the user's legs; and 
extending the user's legs in a running or walking motion so that the elastomeric member stretches and exerts resistance on the user's legs.
